# Day 17 – Load Balancing & Auto Scaling

## Goal
Learn how to distribute traffic and automatically scale EC2 instances.

## Steps
- Launched two EC2 instances in different AZs.
- Created Application Load Balancer and added targets.
- Tested load balancing via ELB DNS name.
- Configured Auto Scaling Group with scaling policies.
- Verified automatic instance creation and termination based on CPU usage.

## Lessons Learned
- ELB distributes traffic evenly across instances.
- Auto Scaling maintains performance and cost efficiency.
- Together, they ensure high availability and fault tolerance.
